    "### 1.3 Who / What / Why / When\n",
    " \n",
    "- **Who:** 10,000 survey respondents whose individual lifestyle choices and estimated carbon emissions have been recorded across 20 variables.\n",
    "- **What:** Apply unsupervised clustering to group respondents into 3–6 behavioural-emission segments based on transport, diet, energy use, waste, and consumption patterns.\n",
    "- **Why:** To enable sustainability organisations and policymakers to move beyond generic carbon-reduction messaging and instead design targeted, equitable interventions matched to each segment's dominant emission drivers.\n",
