    "| 1 | **Pre-analysis equity consultation** | Before clustering (Step 4) | Share objectives and feature list. Ask: \"What does this data miss about your community? What concerns do you have about being categorised?\" |\n",
    "| 2 | **Label review session** | After interpretation (between Steps 5–6) | Present draft labels and personas. Ask: \"Does this feel accurate and fair? Would you be comfortable if your community were described this way?\" Revise any flagged labels. |\n",
    "| 3 | **Impact brief feedback round** | Draft stage (Step 6) | Share recommendations. Ask: \"Would this intervention help your community? What would make it harmful?\" Incorporate feedback before final submission. |\n",
    "| 4 | **Post-delivery community report-back** | 4–6 weeks after submission | Plain-language summary to the community. Explain findings, recommendations, and how community feedback shaped the output. |\n",
    " \n",
    "**Core engagement principles:**\n",
    "- *Nothing about us without us* — no label or recommendation finalised without community input.\n",
    "- *Feedback is binding, not decorative* — if a reviewer flags something as harmful, it is changed.\n",
    "- *Plain language always* — all community-facing materials use everyday language."
